  "text": "+\u03c8 1 [CITATION_1] where\u03c8 1 must satisfy D 2 r\u03c81 = 0 and\u03c8 1 (r \u2192 \u221e) = \u2212r\u0112 0 . Taking\u0112 0 = 1,\u03c8 1 = \u2212r + B/r 2 . On the particle side, and considering that the charge density vanishes atr = 0, the solutions of Equations (22) and (23) are written as:",
